Great Britain 's medal hopes at the 2016 Olympics have taken a hit after potential gold-winning Taekwondo fighter Aaron Cook 's switch to represent Moldova .
The 24-year-old from Dorset , ranked No 2 in the world in the sub-80kg class has had his citizenship change ratified after the breakdown of his relationship with the British Olympic Association .
Cook has been granted Moldovan citizenship and will compete for them in Rio 2016 .